what_worked:
Applied decorrelate, date_cte_isolate: ** Converted nested subqueries to a single CTE using window functions, eliminating redundant scans of store_sales and date_dim. Applied explicit joins and pushed date filter early into a CTE.

**Expected speedup:** ~2.5x by reducing table scans from 3 to 1 and avoiding correlated aggregations.
why_it_worked: Correlated subqueries re-execute per outer row; converting to JOIN eliminates per-row overhead; Pre-filtering date dimension into CTE reduces hash join probe table from 73K to ~365 rows
